Evaluating the two candidates against those points:
- Glen Campbell: described as a cohesive greatest‑hits sequencing (which I accept only when it reads like a unified studio listen), with pristine, close‑mic, lyric‑forward centered vocals, warm midrange and preserved micro‑dynamics/headroom; minimal reverb, preserved transients, restrained guitars/keys and tasteful strings; and polished mastering that emphasizes presence without loudness‑crushing. These attributes hit nearly every preference I stated: close, midrange‑forward vocals that stay lyric‑forward (avoiding harmonies burying the lead); preserved headroom and micro‑dynamics; restrained arrangements and tasteful strings/piano; and transparent mastering and cohesive sequencing that make a greatest‑hits set acceptable because it reads like a unified listen.
