Dislikes: overly dry, close‑miked intimate lead vocals with minimal reverb and excessive headroom; sparse, lo‑fi or thin sonics; mixes that insist on extreme separation and restrained compression at the expense of impact.

The positive CD has the following updated information: Mid‑dominated remaster (Queen — Greatest Hits 1) — bombastic, arena‑polished sound: gated drums, pronounced mid‑band and reverb sheen, compressed punchy low end, denser mixes that lift multitracked vocals (often competing with the lead) and narrowed separation. Ideal for listeners seeking stadium‑scale, late‑’80s glossy processing.

